label.value: regulation of female receptivity

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the willingness or readiness of a female to receive male advances.

label.value: positive regulation of female receptivity

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the receptiveness of a female to male advances.

label.value: negative regulation of growth

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate or extent of growth, the increase in size or mass of all or part of an organism.

label.value: positive regulation of growth

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of growth, the increase in size or mass of all or part of an organism.

label.value: negative regulation of juvenile hormone metabolic process

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving juvenile hormone.

label.value: positive regulation of juvenile hormone metabolic process

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving juvenile hormone.

label.value: negative regulation of mitotic cell cycle

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate or extent of progression through the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: positive regulation of mitotic cell cycle

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of progression through the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: negative regulation of muscle contraction

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of muscle contraction.

label.value: positive regulation of muscle contraction

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of muscle contraction.

label.value: negative regulation of nucleobase-containing compound metabolic process

value.value: Any cellular process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving nucleobases, nucleosides, nucleotides and nucleic acids.

label.value: positive regulation of nucleobase-containing compound metabolic process

value.value: Any cellular process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving nucleobases, nucleosides, nucleotides and nucleic acids.

label.value: negative regulation of phosphate metabolic process

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving phosphates.

label.value: positive regulation of phosphate metabolic process

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving phosphates.

label.value: positive regulation of circadian sleep/wake cycle, sleep

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the duration or quality of sleep, a readily reversible state of reduced awareness and metabolic activity that occurs periodically in many animals.

label.value: negative regulation of steroid metabolic process

label.value: positive regulation of steroid metabolic process

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving steroids.

label.value: negative regulation of phosphorus utilization

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of phosphorus utilization.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription by RNA polymerase I

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription mediated by RNA polymerase I.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription by RNA polymerase II

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription by RNA polymerase III

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription mediated by RNA polymerase III.

label.value: negative regulation of mitotic recombination

value.value: Any process that inhibits or decreases the rate of DNA recombination during mitosis.

label.value: positive regulation of mitotic recombination

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of DNA recombination during mitosis.

label.value: regulation of juvenile hormone catabolic process

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of juvenile hormone.

label.value: positive regulation of complement activation, classical pathway

label.value: negative regulation of development, heterochronic

value.value: Any process that modulates the consistent predetermined time point at which an integrated living unit or organism progresses from an initial condition to a later condition and decreases the rate at which this time point is reached.

label.value: positive regulation of development, heterochronic

value.value: Any process that modulates the consistent predetermined time point at which an integrated living unit or organism progresses from an initial condition to a later condition and increases the rate at which this time point is reached.

label.value: negative regulation of growth rate

value.value: Any process that reduces the rate of growth of all or part of an organism.

definition.value: Note that this term and its definition depart from the usual conventions for GO 'regulation' process terms; regulation of rate is not usually distinguished from regulation of extent or frequency, but it makes sense to do so for growth regulation.

label.value: negative regulation of juvenile hormone biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of juvenile hormone.

label.value: positive regulation of juvenile hormone biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of juvenile hormone.

label.value: positive regulation of juvenile hormone catabolic process

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of juvenile hormone.

label.value: positive regulation of juvenile hormone secretion

label.value: regulation of translation, ncRNA-mediated

value.value: Any process, mediated by small non-coding RNAs, that modulates the frequency, rate or extent that mRNAs are effectively translated into protein.

label.value: positive regulation of translation, ncRNA-mediated

value.value: Any process, mediated by small non-coding RNAs, that activates or increases the rate that mRNAs are effectively translated into protein.
